			<description><![CDATA[<p>Fan Appz is seeking a talented Product Manager to join a dynamic team dedicated to leading the next generation of social media marketing platforms.</p><p><strong>Fan Appz Overview</strong><br />Fan Appz is a leading developer of social media marketing applications used by many of the world&rsquo;s largest brands as well as thousands of smaller businesses to harness the power of social media to acquire new customers and maximize the lifetime value of their fans. We offer a suite of web-based applications that produce effective, highly measurable social media campaigns to spark user engagement, extend viral sharing and promote social competition.&nbsp;Fan Appz is a privately-held company with headquarters in Santa Monica, California, just 2 blocks from the beach!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Product Manager Description</strong><br />The successful Product Manager candidate will have a strong interest and experience in bringing web and mobile products to market, specifically in the social media space.&nbsp; You will initiate and oversee the coordination of products throughout their lifecycle from strategic definition and requirements writing to managing and testing the products.&nbsp; Since you will be working closely with the web designers and developers on a daily basis, a passion for and knowledge of technology and user experience is hugely important.&nbsp; Excellent communication and interpersonal skills and a positive attitude are an absolute must.&nbsp; The Product Manager will report to the Director of Product.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Write product specs and requirements</li><li>Conduct product research</li><li>Work with designers to wireframe and mock up product</li><li>Work with design and engineering teams to prioritize features and define a product roadmap</li><li>Manage project timelines</li><li>Test new products and features in QA environment</li><li>Log improvements and bugs in tracking system</li><li>Update and manage product specifications</li><li>Monitor and optimize products in market</li><li>Train sales and customer service teams on new products</li></ul><p><strong>Required skills and experience:</strong></p><ul><li>BA/BS Required</li><li>3-5 years of comparable experience in online product management, preferably in social media</li><li>Ability to write thorough product requirements and specifications</li><li>Wireframing experience</li><li>Understanding of principles of User Experience</li><li>Proficiency in MS Office</li><li>Familiarity with HTML, CSS, and Photoshop</li><li>Familiarity with and interest in web and mobile social media applications</li><li>Facebook and Twitter savvy</li></ul>]]></description>
